### PART II.

THERE is, then, a state of Being superior to all beings, and to all that
actually is. Being is that by which universal essentiality is common to
all intelligible entities actually existing. . . Nature is sensible
essentiality, including in itself all sensible objects. Midway are the
intellectual and sensible gods. The concepts of intelligence are related
to the intellectual gods, the concepts of opinion to the sensible gods,
which are reflexions of the intelligences; as, for instance, the sun is
the image of the

\[creative

<span id="page_151">p. 151</span>

creative and celestial God. For as God has created the universe, so the
sun creates animals, produces plants, and governs fluid things.

<span class="small">\[These fragments are from Stobæus' Eclogues,
"Physical and Moral."\]</span>

